'''Power push-over''' (Buntover) is the action of an aircraft, typically a [[gyroplane]], whose propeller thrust line is above the [[center of gravity]] and lacks an adequate horizontal stabilizer to pitch forward.

Power push-over is caused by the creation of a [[torque]] around the center of mass of the gyroplane by the force of the propeller and unloading of the rotor. Unloading of the rotor and subsequent power push-over can be caused by excessive pilot-induced oscillations.<ref>{{cite book|title=Rotorcraft Flying Handbook|date=July 1, 2007|publisher=Skyhorse Publishing Inc|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6uoJtGSmQYEC&pg=PT417&dq=Power+Push+over&hl=en&sa=X&ei=rwflVKuNIsL2yQTxu4CwAQ&ved=0CCkQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=Power%20Push%20over&f=false|accessdate=February 18, 2015}}</ref>

