A '''responsibility center''' is an organizational unit headed by a manager, who is responsible for its activities and results.<ref>[[Robert N. Anthony|Anthony, R.]]. ''The Management Control Function,'' Boston, HBS, 1988, p.64.</ref> In [[responsibility accounting]], revenues and cost information are collected and reported on by responsibility centers.<ref>Jae K. Shim; Joel G. Siegel, ''Budgeting Basics and Beyond,'' John Wiley & Sons, {{ISBN|978-0-470-38968-3}}</ref>

Typical examples of responsibility centers are the [[profit center]]<ref>Melumad, Nahum, Dilip Mookherjee, and Stefan Reichelstein. "[http://www0.gsb.columbia.edu/mygsb/faculty/research/pubfiles/1985/1985.pdf A theory of responsibility centers]." ''Journal of Accounting and Economics'' 15.4 (1992): 445-484.</ref> and the [[Cost centre (business)|cost center]].

